  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SITE SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Supervise daily site activities and ensure works are carried out according to approved drawings and specifications</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and manage site workers, subcontractors, and resources</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) and quality standards</p></li><li><p>Monitor work progress, productivity, and site conditions</p></li><li><p>Maintain daily site records and report site issues, delays, or changes</p></li><li><p>Assist in site reporting and documentation</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>2 years’ experience</strong> in construction site supervision</p></li><li><p>Good knowledge of <strong>road construction methods, materials, and safety regulations</strong></p></li><li><p>Able to read and interpret construction drawings</p></li><li><p>Familiar with WSH requirements</p></li><li><p>Independent, responsible, and able to work well with site teams</p></li><li><p>Posses valid class 3 driving license is an advantage</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
